adjectives.description: incalculable (comparative more incalculable, superlative most incalculable)

entries.meaning: (not comparable) Too much, too vast, or too numerous to enable computation.
examples: The loss the National Library suffered from the fire is incalculable.

entries.meaning: (comparable) Of a person's mood or character, etc.: impossible to predict.
examples: He is incalculable when he's drunk. He can turn from an amiable person into a violent horror in a moment.
